With summer quickly approaching, I wanted to take the opportunity to remind you of the importance of personalized one on one make-up sessions. To help you better apply your make up for the hot weather this summer, it’s important to have the right tools and techniques that will make your make-up sweat proof and last longer.

One on one sessions can help you achieve a perfect summer make-up look that will leave you looking beautiful and refreshed all day long. During these sessions, we’ll work together to help you learn the best techniques to apply your make-up and create a look that will last all day without smudging or melting off.

we will also be offering shopping trips to help you to pick out the specific products you need in order to enhance that personalize make up application

"I'm not doing all that shit." 😡

Those were the words I muttered as I researched the ingredients for beef stroganoff. I had never made it before, but watching a video online made me want it so badly. 

When I looked at the ingredients, it seemed like it would require so many ingredients and so much time to make it correctly. This was not something that I was going to be able to create off the top of my head or miss using ingredients .

 I would have to use specific things, and it would take me more ingredients and more time. 

However, I want to encourage you that there are many times in our lives that will require more than we are prepared for, but we have all the proper ingredients to make it work. Look deep down within yourself and find the strength to finish it, so that life can begin to taste just as it should.

The average amount of time I spend on the bridesmaid, of course, is substantially less and the bride but darling, you’ve never be able to tell!

One of my favorite ways to approach make up for bridesmaids is to make him compliment Bride, but not overpower her look.

1. I create a uniform look for every bridesmaid because everybody’s face is different. Then Makeup is going to read different with everybody so you don’t have to worry about something looking too bold or too soft, because I’m always going to pick something that fits everyone ! 

2. There is no nice way to say this, but the day is about the Bride so I don’t like to get into too many particulars about what the bridesmaids want although I want him to feel special we want to focus to be on the bride.

3. Because I customize my luxe, I make sure that the person is still satisfied so if there are things that you just simply do not want as a part of your make up, I will accommodate that.

#okcmua #okcbridalmakeup #bridesofoklahoma #softglam

If you know me, then you know I love Kim Kardashian, but in reality a lot of people who come to me it is their first time getting their make up done, and they pick images for special events that are so far from what they would normally wear if they even wanna make it all and then they are overwhelmed and unsatisfied so here is a quick tip for picking out your make up reference photos for your make up application.

1. Think about your relationship with Makeup if you’ve never worn, make up before this may or may not be the time to do some thing far off automatic because you may not like it.

2. Think of people who you admire and think of the shows you watch on TV to help you find something that feels more like you.

3. Let’s just say for instance you do wanna do some thing a little bit more dramatic figure out what area of the face you want the drama to be focused on do you want a more  dramatic I do you want him automatic lip. The choice is yours.

#makeuptips #makeupforbeginners #makeuptutorial #makeupkit
